The paper deals with resource allocation in non-orthogonal interference networks, which is a topic related to information theory and networked systems. Therefore, cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also discusses numerical optimization algorithms, which falls under cs.SY (Systems and Control) and cs.MA (Machine Learning). Finally, the paper presents experimental results, which could be relevant to cs.LG (Machine Learning).
